[20]In 1512, during an Imperial Diet Emperor Maximilian I demanded to see the Holy Robe which was kept in the Cathedral.
[21]Archbishop Richard von Greiffenklau arranged the opening of the altar that had enshrined the tunic since the building of the Dome and exhibited it.
